MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: \.claude/guardrails/.+\.rule$
MATCH_CONTENT: ^(trigger:|glob:|---[[:space:]]*$)
ADVISORY: |
  Rule file appears to use YAML frontmatter format (`---` / `trigger:` / `glob:`).
  The guardian hook parses `MATCH_TOOL:` / `MATCH_PATTERN:` / `MATCH_CONTENT:` /
  `ADVISORY:` only — unmatched fields are silently treated as "always pass," so
  a YAML-frontmatter rule fires on EVERY tool call, injecting its full advisory
  body into the next agent's context.

  Correct format:

    MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
    MATCH_PATTERN: apps/foo/src/bar\.ts$
    MATCH_CONTENT: (optional regex on edit body)
    ADVISORY: |
      Short advisory text here.

  See .claude/guardrails/README.md for details.
